# CODEOWNERS — who must review what.
#
# GitHub uses this file to auto-request reviews when a PR touches matching paths.
# The rules are evaluated bottom-up; the LAST matching rule wins.
#
# This repo is the AI-SRE agent system. Different parts of the codebase have
# very different review needs:
#
#   - personas/   — the agents' system prompts. A bad change can silently
#                   change behaviour across thousands of incidents, so this
#                   needs human SRE-lead review even when the diff is small.
#   - runbooks/   — operational knowledge. Tech lead + on-call rotation owner.
#   - .github/    — automation. A bad GHA workflow can leak tokens or
#                   open thousands of PRs — needs infra review.
#   - src/sre_agent/winner.py + autorunbook.py — the L6 self-improvement
#                   code path. Touches model behaviour, needs ML/SRE review.
#
# Replace @your-org/* placeholders with your real team handles before
# enabling branch protection.

# ── Default: anyone on the core team can review ───────────────────────────
*                                  @your-org/sre-agent-core

# ── L6 self-improvement code (the model-behaviour pipeline) ───────────────
/src/sre_agent/winner.py           @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform
/src/sre_agent/autorunbook.py      @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform
/src/sre_agent/seed.py             @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform
/tests/test_winner.py              @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform
/tests/test_autorunbook.py         @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform
/tests/test_seed.py                @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/ml-platform

# ── Personas — auto-generated promotions need an SRE-lead approval ────────
# (The harness-winner GHA opens PRs that ONLY touch personas/. CODEOWNERS
# guarantees a human SRE lead must approve before the new prompt ships.)
/personas/                         @your-org/sre-leads
/personas/variants/                @your-org/sre-leads @your-org/sre-agent-core

# ── Runbooks — knowledge artefacts; service-team owners ───────────────────
# (The harness-autorunbook GHA stages drafts under runbooks/_drafts/. The
# service team that owns the affected service must approve before
# promoting a draft into the indexed runbook set.)
/runbooks/                         @your-org/sre-oncall-rotation
/runbooks/_drafts/                 @your-org/sre-oncall-rotation @your-org/sre-agent-core

# ── Automation — workflows and CI scripts ─────────────────────────────────
/.github/workflows/                @your-org/sre-agent-core @your-org/infra
/scripts/                          @your-org/sre-agent-core

# ── Dashboard (Flask + JS) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
/dashboard/                        @your-org/sre-agent-core

# ── Tutorial site & docs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
/docs/                             @your-org/sre-agent-core
/README.md                         @your-org/sre-agent-core
